":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"key":"K6CVaPOkFN"}],"key":"ub9tUsNlBp"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"All of these questions attempt to assign a cause to an effect. A careful\nexamination of data can help shed light on questions like these. In this section\nyou will learn some of the fundamental concepts involved in establishing\ncausality.","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"G9e3xRFYlw"}],"key":"tEAdEtoHDJ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Observation is a key to good science. An ","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"YzjF9mpxQF"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"observational study","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"hTH9MXsZYC"}],"key":"W9xJBm5PxT"},{"type":"text","value":" is one in which\nscientists make conclusions based on data that they have observed but had no\nhand in generating. In data science, many such studies involve observations on a\ngroup of individuals, a factor of interest called a ","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"UOZvGJ0lh7"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"treatment","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"jZlwmt5u7Q"}],"key":"QlVT0GvhPe"},{"type":"text","value":", and an\n","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"AhDr4ujNw6"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"outcome","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"WpTFVCo1F8"}],"key":"UyPJ1HZTgf"},{"type":"text","value":" measured on each individual.","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"YCsl2QKL0t"}],"key":"YGSxqCBA7T"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It is easiest to think of the individuals as people. In a study of whether\nchocolate is good for the health, the individuals would indeed be people, the\ntreatment would be eating chocolate, and the outcome might be a measure of heart disease. But individuals in observational studies need not be people. In a\nstudy of whether the death penalty has a deterrent effect, the individuals could\nbe the 50 states of the union. A state law allowing the death penalty would be\nthe treatment, and an outcome could be the state’s murder rate.","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":23,"column":1}},"key":"GtjWXvlxEW"}],"key":"BBkq5EE76b"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The fundamental question is whether the treatment has an effect on the outcome.\nAny relation between the treatment and the outcome is called an ","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"sNnKAkhut8"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"association","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"NGcH1YypbD"}],"key":"Fk6nHTktPy"},{"type":"text","value":".\nIf the treatment causes the outcome to occur, then the association is ","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"gVA1p2bPXW"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"causal","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"PtfnNkgJA5"}],"key":"BhJ3IyXTwI"},{"type":"text","value":".\n","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"lH5xlEUNDJ"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Causality","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"tBgAkY8gzR"}],"key":"JRroOEU1We"},{"type":"text","value":" is at the heart of all three questions posed at the start of this\nsection. For example, one of the questions was whether chocolate directly causes\nimprovements in health, not just whether there is a relation between\nchocolate and health.","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"riY2Ef2vwJ"}],"key":"SdOwAphncw"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":38,"column":1},"end":{"line":40,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The establishment of causality often takes place in two stages. First, an\nassociation is observed. Next, a more careful analysis leads to a decision about\ncausality.","position":{"start":{"line":38,"column":1},"end":{"line":38,"column":1}},"key":"KE3qt5JoQP"}],"key":"esqpygYJ1o"}],"key":"tZdymPyB3d"}],"key":"HLHmScO064"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"Another Kind of Character","url":"/chapters/01/3/2/another-kind-of-character","group":"Computational and Inferential Thinking"},"next":{"title":"Observation and Visualization: John Snow and the Broad Street Pump","url":"/chapters/02/1/observation-and-visualization-john-snow-and-the-br","group":"Computational and Inferential Thinking"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3000"}